        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 10:47PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1046 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Madisonville, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crockett, Madisonville, Austonio, and Lovelady.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
southeastern Texas.</instruction>
